place.name: HUNWORTH
place.gazetteerText: HUNWORTH, a parish in Erpingham district, Norfolk; on the rivulet Glaven, 2 miles SSW of Holt, and 9½ NE of Ryburgh r. station. Post town, Holt, under Thetford. Acres, 838. Real property, £1, 210. Pop., 206. Houses, 48. The property is divided among a few. The manor belongs to the Marquis of Lothian. The living is a rectory, annexed to the rectory of Stody, in the diocese of Norwich. The church is later English, in pretty good condition; and consists of nave, S transept, and chancel, with porch and tower. There is a school with £6 from endowment. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
